{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "http://localhost:3000/workspace/f3426eb9-7e45-4109-8d64-fcbada5245b3/2a04aef1-eb6e-4a61-a82f-aac96099c22a \n\nOn the Workspace Details page for each page, we want to add a new tab called KANBAN. This would show the same KANBAN board as the main app KANBAN, but would be scoped just to tasks that are associated with that smart role. This would make it easier for people to be able to scan through all of their pages and then be able to see tasks that were assigned to them by viewing the Kanban board, without having to jump to the Kanban board.\n\nI think on the Kanban board we could also add some filtering so that we could filter by the smart role as well. Can you think deeply about this? Our goal is to make it easier for users to discover content and reduce the amount of head space needed to keep track of which pages have which information on them. ",
